    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-05-26T15:55:37+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-26T15:55:37+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-26T06:25:37Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-26T06:25:37Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A low pressure system lies north of Kangaroo Island and is expected to move north and over the Eyre Peninsula and towards the Flinders district today, weakening as it moves into NSW on Wednesday. A weak ridge of high pressure begins to move across SA mid week. A cold front is expected to move over the west and southeast of SA on Friday. A high pressure system moves into the west on Saturday and then moves into the north on Sunday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW010" description="West Coast" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-05-26T15:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-27T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-26T05:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-26T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers west of Ceduna, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm east of Ceduna. Winds southwesterly 25 to 35 km/h decreasing to 15 to 20 km/h in the late evening.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-05-27T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-28T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-26T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-27T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Patchy morning fog south of Streaky Bay. Medium chance of showers west of Nullarbor, slight chance elsewhere. Winds south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h becoming light in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching around 20.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 11:10am to 1:50pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-05-28T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-29T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-27T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-28T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Slight chance of a shower south of Streaky Bay, near zero chance elsewhere. Light winds becoming north to northwesterly 15 to 20 km/h in the morning then becoming light in the late afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 7 with daytime temperatures reaching between 18 and 21.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-05-29T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-30T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-28T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-29T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. The chance of morning fog south of Streaky Bay. Medium chance of showers south of Streaky Bay, slight chance elsewhere. Winds north to northwesterly 15 to 20 km/h turning west to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to around 10 with daytime temperatures reaching the low 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-05-30T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-31T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-29T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-30T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog west of Ceduna. High chance of showers east of Ceduna, slight chance elsewhere. Winds west to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h tending west to southwesterly during the afternoon then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 10 with daytime temperatures reaching between 17 and 21.</text>
            </forecast-period>
